import org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession
import org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession._
import org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row
import org.apache.spark.sql.types.{StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType, LongType, DoubleType, TimestampType}


/**
 * This doesn't actually read pcaps.  It reads the csv files produced by tshark in Vu's script.
 */
object pcapReader {

  
  /**
   * Fields in the file are:
   * 1. frame.number 
   * 2. frame.time_epoch 
   * 3. ip.src 
   * 4. tcp.srcport 
   * 5. ip.dst 
   * 6. tcp.dstport 
   * 7. ip.proto 
   * 8. frame.len 
   * 9. tcp.seq 
   * 10. tcp.ack 
   * 11. tcp.options.mptcp.rawdataseqno 
   * 12. tcp.options.mptcp.rawdataack
   * 
   * 
   */
	val pcapSchema = StructType(Array(
			StructField("framenumber", LongType, false),
			StructField("timestamp", DoubleType, true),
			StructField("src", StringType, false),
			StructField("srcport", IntegerType, false),
			StructField("dst", StringType, true),
			StructField("dstport", IntegerType, false),
			StructField("proto", IntegerType, true),
			StructField("framelen", IntegerType, true),
			StructField("tcpseq", IntegerType, true),
			StructField("tcpack", IntegerType, true),
			StructField("dsn", LongType, true),  // because there is no unsigned 32 bit type afaik
			StructField("dack", LongType, true)));

	/**
	 * read in the task events file(s)
	 */
	def readPcap(spark: SparkSession, filename: String): Dataset[Row] = {
			return spark.read
					.option("sep","\t")
				  .option("nullValue","NULL")
				  .option("mode","DROPMALFORMED")
				  .schema(pcapSchema)
				  .csv(filename)
	}
	
}

import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window

def loadProcessPcapLatency(srcfile:String, dstfile:String): Dataset[Row] = {
    val first_w = Window.partitionBy($"proto", $"dstport", $"dsn", $"dack").orderBy($"timestamp".asc)

    val src_pcap = pcapReader.readPcap(spark, "/home/ikt/short-no-outage/iperf-interupted-lowrtt-on10-off3-sender-1.csv")
        .filter("proto=6").filter("dsn is not null").filter("dack is not null")
        .withColumn("rn", row_number.over(first_w)).where("rn=1").drop("rn")
    val dst_pcap = pcapReader.readPcap(spark, "/home/ikt/short-no-outage/iperf-interupted-lowrtt-on10-off3-receiver-1.csv")
        .filter("proto=6").filter("dsn is not null").filter("dack is not null")
        .withColumn("rn", row_number.over(first_w)).where("rn=1").drop("rn")

    return src_pcap.as("src").join(dst_pcap.as("dst"), $"src.proto"===$"dst.proto" && $"src.dst"===$"dst.dst" && $"src.dstport"===$"dst.dstport" && $"src.dsn"===$"dst.dsn" && $"src.dack"===$"dst.dack")
    .drop("proto").drop($"dst.src").drop("srcport").drop($"dst.dst").drop("dstport").drop($"dst.framelen").drop($"dst.dsn").drop($"dst.dack")
    .withColumn("latency", $"dst.timestamp" - $"src.timestamp")
    
}

import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
{
 
import spark.implicits._
   
val first_w = Window.partitionBy($"proto", $"dsn", $"dack").orderBy($"timestamp".asc)
val sorted_w = Window.orderBy($"timestamp".asc)
val jt_sorted_w = Window.orderBy($"timestamp".asc)
val taskid_w = Window.partitionBy($"jobid").orderBy($"timestamp".asc)

val src_pcap = pcapReader.readPcap(spark, "/home/ikt/short-no-outage/iperf-interupted-re-on10-off3-sender-1.csv")
        .filter("proto=6").filter("dsn is not null").filter("dack is not null")

// unfortunately there's no way to assign an ordering and dense rank to the partitions.
// otherwise we could compute the job and task IDs at the same time.
// dense_rank doesn't do it because we want to partition by one thing, but order by timestamp.
// This will compute job IDs by grouping the src packets by (dst,dstport,dsn,dack),
// taking the first row from each partition, and then assigning a rank to those representatives.
val jobid_index = src_pcap.withColumn("rn", row_number.over(first_w)).where("rn=1").drop("rn")
    .withColumn("jobid", row_number.over(sorted_w))
    .drop("timestamp", "framenumber", "proto", "tcpseq", "tcpack", "framelen", "src", "srcport", "dstport")
println("jobid_index")
jobid_index.show()

// now we have to join this back onto the source_pcap
// and on the last line, compute the task IDs
val jsrc_pcap = src_pcap.as("src").join(jobid_index.as("job"), $"src.dst"===$"job.dst" && $"src.dsn"===$"job.dsn" && $"src.dack"===$"job.dack")
        .withColumn("taskid", row_number.over(taskid_w))
        .withColumn("tasknum", row_number.over(jt_sorted_w))
        .drop($"job.dst").drop($"job.dsn").drop($"job.dack")
println("jsrc_pcap")
jsrc_pcap.orderBy("timestamp").show()
println("jsrc_pcap resends")
jsrc_pcap.filter("taskid>1").orderBy("timestamp").show()

        
val taskid_index = jsrc_pcap.select("jobid", "taskid", "tasknum", "dst", "dsn", "dack", "tcpseq", "tcpack")
println("taskid_index")
taskid_index.orderBy("jobid","taskid").show()

val dst_pcap = pcapReader.readPcap(spark, "/home/ikt/short-no-outage/iperf-interupted-re-on10-off3-receiver-1.csv")
        .filter("proto=6").filter("dsn is not null").filter("dack is not null")
println("dst_pcap")
dst_pcap.show()

val jdst_pcap = dst_pcap.as("dst").join(taskid_index.as("p"), $"dst.dst"===$"p.dst" && $"dst.dsn"===$"p.dsn" && $"dst.dack"===$"p.dack" && $"dst.tcpseq"===$"p.tcpseq" && $"dst.tcpack"===$"p.tcpack", "left_outer")
    .filter($"tasknum".isNotNull)
    .drop($"p.dst").drop($"p.dsn").drop($"p.dack").drop($"p.tcpseq").drop($"p.tcpack")
       //.drop("p.dst", "p.dstport", "p.dsn", "p.dack", "p.tcpseq", "p.tcpack")
    
//val mp_packet_index2 = mp_packet_index.withColumn("taskid", row_number.over(taskid_w))

//.drop("timestamp", "framenumber", "proto", "tcpseq", "tcpack", "framelen", "src", "srcport")

//mp_packet_index2.filter("taskid>1").show()

println("jdst_pcap")
jdst_pcap.orderBy("timestamp").show(50)

println("1st sends = "+jdst_pcap.filter("taskid=1").count())
println("2nd sends = "+jdst_pcap.filter("taskid=2").count())
println("unmatched dst packets")
jdst_pcap.filter($"tasknum".isNull).show()

val jpcap = jsrc_pcap.as("src").join(dst_pcap.as("dst"), $"dst.dst"===$"src.dst" && $"dst.dstport"===$"src.dstport" && $"dst.dsn"===$"src.dsn" && $"dst.dack"===$"src.dack" && $"dst.tcpseq"===$"src.tcpseq" && $"dst.tcpack"===$"src.tcpack", "left_outer")
    .drop($"dst.src").drop($"dst.srcport").drop($"dst.dst").drop($"dst.dstport").drop($"dst.proto").drop($"dst.framelen").drop($"dst.tcpseq").drop($"dst.tcpack").drop($"dst.dsn").drop($"dst.dack").drop($"dst.framenumber").drop($"src.framenumber")
println("number of src packets = "+src_pcap.count())
println("number of jsrc packets = "+jsrc_pcap.count())
println("number of joined packets = "+jpcap.count())

println("number of dst packets = "+dst_pcap.count())
println("number of jdst packets = "+jdst_pcap.count())

println("flawed src rows")
src_pcap.filter($"dst".isNull).show()

println("un-matched (dropped) src packets")
jpcap.filter($"dst.timestamp".isNull).orderBy("tasknum").show()

}

       legend=Legend(orient="left", title="timestamp"))
    .encodeDetailFields(Field(field="symbol", dataType=Nominal))
    .show
